This paper is about distributed software-defined networks (SDN), which is a topic related to computer networks and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses network structural properties and synchronization strategies, which are related to complex systems (cs.SI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also uses analytical methods for performance estimation, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY).
